# Data Flow — Complete Visual Guide

## The Simple Version First

Think of it like ordering food at a restaurant:

```
YOU order food → Waiter takes order → Kitchen cooks → Waiter brings food → YOU eat
```

In our project:
```
YOU send request → Controller receives → Service processes → Repository saves → Database stores
                                                                    ↓
YOU get response ← Controller returns ← Service returns ← Repository fetches ← Database
```

---

## Part 1 — The 5 Layers and Their Jobs

Before understanding flow, understand who does what:

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                                                                 │
│   LAYER 1 → Security Filter    "Is this person allowed in?"    │
│                ↓                                                │
│   LAYER 2 → Controller         "What do you want?"             │
│                ↓                                                │
│   LAYER 3 → Service            "Let me process that"           │
│                ↓                                                │
│   LAYER 4 → Repository         "Let me talk to the database"   │
│                ↓                                                │
│   LAYER 5 → Database           "I will store/retrieve data"    │
│                                                                 │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

Real world comparison:

```
Security Filter  =  Security guard at office entrance
Controller       =  Receptionist who receives your request
Service          =  Manager who decides what to do
Repository       =  Filing clerk who goes to the cabinet
Database         =  The actual filing cabinet with all records
```

