## Part 2 — CREATE Flow (POST Request)

### Scenario: You want to add a new item "Wireless Mouse"

```
STEP 1 — You send this from Swagger/Postman:
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
POST http://localhost:8081/api/items

Headers:
  Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9.xxxxx

Body (JSON):
{
  "name": "Wireless Mouse",
  "description": "Ergonomic mouse",
  "category": "Electronics"
}
```

```
STEP 2 — JwtAuthFilter.java runs FIRST (before anything else)
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

  Reads header: "Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGc..."
        ↓
  Extracts the token: "eyJhbGc..."
        ↓
  Calls jwtUtil.validateToken(token)
        ↓
  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │ Valid token? → YES → continue request   │
  │ Valid token? → NO  → return 401 error   │
  │              STOP, nothing else runs    │
  └─────────────────────────────────────────┘
        ↓ (token was valid, so continue)
```

```
STEP 3 — ItemController.java receives the request
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

  @PostMapping → createItem() method is called
        ↓
  Spring reads the JSON body and converts it to ItemDTO object:

  ItemDTO {
    id          = null  (not provided yet)
    name        = "Wireless Mouse"
    description = "Ergonomic mouse"
    category    = "Electronics"
    createdAt   = null  (not provided yet)
  }
        ↓
  @Valid annotation triggers validation:
  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │ name blank?     NO → ✓ pass                            │
  │ name > 150?     NO → ✓ pass                            │
  │ category blank? NO → ✓ pass                            │
  │ All passed → continue to service                       │
  │ Any failed → return 400 Bad Request immediately        │
  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
        ↓ (all validation passed)
  Calls: itemService.createItem(itemDTO)
```

```
STEP 4 — ItemServiceImpl.java processes the request
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

  Receives: ItemDTO object

  Converts DTO → Model (Entity):

  ItemDTO (what came in)    →    Item (database object)
  ┌──────────────────┐           ┌──────────────────────┐
  │ name: W. Mouse   │    →      │ name: W. Mouse        │
  │ desc: Ergo mouse │    →      │ description: Ergo..   │
  │ category: Electr │    →      │ category: Electronics │
  │ createdAt: null  │    →      │ createdAt: 2025-07-28 │ ← set NOW
  └──────────────────┘           └──────────────────────┘

  Why convert? DTO is for outside world, Model is for database.
        ↓
  Calls: itemRepository.save(item)
```

```
STEP 5 — ItemRepository.java talks to MySQL
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

  Receives: Item object

  Hibernate (JPA) automatically generates SQL:

  INSERT INTO items (name, description, category, created_at)
  VALUES ('Wireless Mouse', 'Ergonomic mouse', 'Electronics', '2025-07-28 09:00:00')

  Sends this SQL to MySQL database
        ↓
```

```
STEP 6 — MySQL Database saves the data
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

  items table BEFORE:
  ┌────┬──────┬─────────┬──────────┬────────────┐
  │ id │ name │  desc   │ category │ created_at │
  ├────┼──────┼─────────┼──────────┼────────────┤
  │    │      │  EMPTY  │          │            │
  └────┴──────┴─────────┴──────────┴────────────┘

  items table AFTER:
  ┌────┬──────────────┬──────────────┬─────────────┬─────────────────────┐
  │ id │ name         │ description  │ category    │ created_at          │
  ├────┼──────────────┼──────────────┼─────────────┼─────────────────────┤
  │  1 │ Wireless     │ Ergonomic    │ Electronics │ 2025-07-28 09:00:00 │
  │    │ Mouse        │ mouse        │             │                     │
  └────┴──────────────┴──────────────┴─────────────┴─────────────────────┘

  MySQL returns the saved row WITH the auto-generated id=1
        ↓
```

```
STEP 7 — Response travels back UP through the layers
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

  Repository returns: Item object (with id=1 now set)
        ↓
  Service converts Item → ItemDTO:

  Item (from database)        →    ItemDTO (to send back)
  ┌───────────────────┐            ┌───────────────────┐
  │ id: 1             │     →      │ id: 1             │
  │ name: W. Mouse    │     →      │ name: W. Mouse    │
  │ category: Electr  │     →      │ category: Electr  │
  │ createdAt: ...    │     →      │ createdAt: ...    │
  └───────────────────┘            └───────────────────┘
        ↓
  Controller wraps it in ApiResponse:
  {
    "success": true,
    "message": "Item created successfully",
    "data": {
      "id": 1,
      "name": "Wireless Mouse",
      "description": "Ergonomic mouse",
      "category": "Electronics",
      "createdAt": "2025-07-28T09:00:00"
    }
  }
        ↓
  HTTP Status 201 Created sent back to YOU
```

