## Part 3 — READ Flow (GET Request)

### Scenario: You want to get item with id=1

```
YOU → GET http://localhost:8081/api/items/1
      Authorization: Bearer token
           ↓
JwtAuthFilter → token valid? YES → continue
           ↓
Controller → getItemById(1) called
           ↓
Service → calls itemRepository.findById(1)
           ↓
Repository → generates SQL:
  SELECT * FROM items WHERE id = 1
           ↓
Database → finds the row, returns it
           ↓
           ┌──────────────────────────────────────┐
           │ Found?                               │
           │  YES → convert to DTO → return 200  │
           │  NO  → throw ItemNotFoundException  │
           │        → GlobalExceptionHandler     │
           │        → return 404 Not Found       │
           └──────────────────────────────────────┘
           ↓ (found)
YOU receive:
{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Item retrieved successfully",
  "data": { "id": 1, "name": "Wireless Mouse", ... }
}
```

