## Part 4 — UPDATE Flow (PUT Request)

### Scenario: Change "Wireless Mouse" category to "Accessories"

```
YOU → PUT http://localhost:8081/api/items/1
Body: {
  "name": "Wireless Mouse",
  "description": "Ergonomic mouse",
  "category": "Accessories"   ← changed this
}
           ↓
JwtAuthFilter → token check → valid
           ↓
Controller → updateItem(id=1, itemDTO) called
           ↓
Service:
  Step 1: Find existing item
          itemRepository.findById(1)
          → SELECT * FROM items WHERE id = 1
          → Found: {id:1, name:"Wireless Mouse", category:"Electronics"}

  Step 2: Update the fields
          item.setCategory("Accessories")  ← only category changed
          item.setName("Wireless Mouse")   ← same
          item.setDescription("Ergo...")   ← same

  Step 3: Save it back
          itemRepository.save(item)
          → UPDATE items SET category='Accessories'
            WHERE id = 1
           ↓
Database updates the row:
  BEFORE: {id:1, name:"Wireless Mouse", category:"Electronics"}
  AFTER:  {id:1, name:"Wireless Mouse", category:"Accessories"}
           ↓
YOU receive:
{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Item updated successfully",
  "data": { "id": 1, "name": "Wireless Mouse", "category": "Accessories" }
}
```

