## Part 5 — DELETE Flow (DELETE Request)

### Scenario: Delete item with id=1

```
YOU → DELETE http://localhost:8081/api/items/1
           ↓
JwtAuthFilter → token check → valid
           ↓
Controller → deleteItem(1) called
           ↓
Service:
  Step 1: Does item exist?
          itemRepository.existsById(1)
          → SELECT COUNT(*) FROM items WHERE id = 1
          ┌──────────────────────────────────────────┐
          │ Exists? YES → proceed to delete          │
          │ Exists? NO  → throw ItemNotFoundException│
          │               return 404 Not Found       │
          └──────────────────────────────────────────┘

  Step 2: Delete it
          itemRepository.deleteById(1)
          → DELETE FROM items WHERE id = 1
           ↓
Database:
  BEFORE: row with id=1 exists
  AFTER:  row with id=1 is gone permanently
           ↓
YOU receive:
{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Item deleted successfully",
  "data": null
}
HTTP Status: 200 OK
```

