## Part 6 — Error Flow (What Happens When Things Go Wrong)

### Scenario 1: Invalid JWT Token

```
YOU → GET /api/items/1
      Authorization: Bearer INVALID_TOKEN
           ↓
JwtAuthFilter:
  jwtUtil.validateToken("INVALID_TOKEN") → false
           ↓
  Request BLOCKED here itself
  Controller never even runs
           ↓
YOU receive: HTTP 403 Forbidden
```

### Scenario 2: Validation Fails

```
YOU → POST /api/items
Body: {
  "name": "",           ← empty! not allowed
  "category": ""        ← empty! not allowed
}
           ↓
JwtAuthFilter → token valid → continue
           ↓
Controller:
  @Valid checks ItemDTO:
  name is blank → FAIL
  category is blank → FAIL
           ↓
  GlobalExceptionHandler catches this
           ↓
YOU receive: HTTP 400 Bad Request
{
  "success": false,
  "message": "Validation failed",
  "data": {
    "name": "Name is required",
    "category": "Category is required"
  }
}
  Controller never even calls Service
  Service never even runs
  Database never even touched
```

### Scenario 3: Item Not Found

```
YOU → GET /api/items/999
           ↓
JwtAuthFilter → valid
           ↓
Controller → getItemById(999)
           ↓
Service → itemRepository.findById(999)
           ↓
Repository → SELECT * FROM items WHERE id = 999
           ↓
Database → no row found → returns empty
           ↓
Service:
  .orElseThrow(() -> new ItemNotFoundException(999))
  throws: ItemNotFoundException("Item not found with id: 999")
           ↓
GlobalExceptionHandler catches ItemNotFoundException
           ↓
YOU receive: HTTP 404 Not Found
{
  "success": false,
  "message": "Item not found with id: 999",
  "data": null
}
```

