## Part 9 — Summary Table

| Action | You Send | SQL Generated | You Get Back |
|--------|----------|---------------|--------------|
| Create | POST + JSON body | INSERT INTO | 201 + new record |
| Read one | GET + id in URL | SELECT WHERE id=? | 200 + record |
| Read all | GET | SELECT * FROM | 200 + list |
| Update | PUT + id + JSON | UPDATE SET WHERE id=? | 200 + updated record |
| Delete | DELETE + id | DELETE WHERE id=? | 200 + success message |
| Not found | any + wrong id | SELECT returns empty | 404 + error message |
| Bad input | POST + empty fields | never reaches DB | 400 + validation errors |
| No token | any + no header | never reaches DB | 403 + unauthorized |

That is the complete data flow of this entire project. Every request, every service, every scenario follows this same pattern.
